features: Easy & Efficient Printing: The thermal printer features a user-friendly design with simple controls, making it easy for anyone to use. Advanced thermal printing technology no need for ink or toner, to keep away from stains, effectively reducing the cost of supplies. Rohm print head ensures clear print quality even at high speeds and continuous printing.

Bluetooth for Mobile Phone: MUNBYN RealWriter 130 Bluetooth label printer, supports Bluetooth connection for iOS and Android systems, and prints labels anytime, anywhere. Download the "MUNBYN print" app for quick and easy label printing.

USB for PC: MUNBYN RealWriter 130 Bluetooth Thermal label printer specially configured with a USB cable for macOS, Windows (7 and later) system computers. You can even add "MUNBYN Printer" extensions on Chrome browser for Chromebook use. (Note that Laptop and Desktop only work with a USB connection, you can not print via Bluetooth.)

Portable and High Definition: Weighing only 2.3 pounds, this shipping label printer is easy to carry either on business or on the go. 203DIP clarity helps identify bar codes quickly. 180 mm/sec ultra-fast print speed lets you save time and money.

Wide Compatibility: The Bluetooth thermal printer is compatible with eBay, Etsy, Shopify, UPS, and other major shipping and shopping platforms. Suitable for direct thermal labels with widths ranging from 1.57" to 4.3", including envelope labels, package labels, address labels, barcode labels, and labels for home and office.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Why can not connect to the printer? 1. Make sure the printer is turned on (Green light is on) 2. Bluetooth can only be used to connect phones or tablets, the computer needs to be connected with a USB cable How to print with Google Chrome? 1. Connecting printer and computer via USB cable 2. Add "MUNBYN printer'' to the Chrome extension 3. Click "Add" to find your printer and complete the print settings 4. Open the file in Chrome, "Ctrl+P", select the printer you added, click ‘’Print‘’ (1)How to connect the 130B printer by Bluetooth on a Windows laptop? 1. Turn on the laptop Bluetooth then connect ITPP130B-1D6A 2. Click "Settings"-"Bluetooth and Devices"-"More Bluetooth Settings"- "COM Ports" 3. Remember the outgoing direction corresponding port ... (2)How to connect the 130B printer by Bluetooth on a Windows laptop? 4. Go back to "Bluetooth and Devices"-"Printers and Scanners"-Click on"ITPP130 Printer" 5. Switch to the same port as ITPP130B-1D6A The Bluetooth connection has been completed, you can unplug the USB cable now.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Connects quickly, prints super fast
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I’ll keep the review fairly short and simple. Build quality is good, mostly plastic but feels sturdy. Instructions somewhat vague, but once you connect it to the app it’s pretty simple to get it up and running. It prints fairly good quality and VERY fast (impressively so). It is a bit on the louder side, but I mean it’s a printer, you can’t expect it to be quiet. It takes a good variety of sticker types, however keep in mind to adjust the little plastic guide rails inside based on which sticker size you’re using (I couldn’t figure out at first why my prints were crooked)App could use some work to make it a little better optimized for cellphones(dials and buttons are small) otherwise it works fine. Overall solid little printer, good bang for the buck4.5/5 stars

reviews.reviewText: I had bought a different thermal printer previously and it was a PAIN to use, but this one is PERFECT! I love that I can print from my phone or iPad via Bluetooth. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I love this printer for printing labels on eBay. I tried to make 2x3 labels with a message about returns for our customers, but was not able to do so because 2x3 labels wasn’t a size selection available in the print screen. But I can say this printer prints shipping labels like a beast and is superior to my brother thermal printer in every way: loading new labels is a breeze, no jams, never prints a blank label along with a printed label, and prints immediately. I used their brand of labels and they have the best adhesion. In the past, I had labels on boxes where the edges would curl up if left sitting indoors overnight. But their brand of labels stay put. The printer prints clearly and there are never any smudgy looking labels. It’s such a great machine. I’ve had it since the summer and it makes the shipping process easier and even more enjoyable. As for the return label memo, I may try a 2x2 size in the future, which is one of their print options (along with many other size options). I did call their company about it and they called me within minutes and were very nice. They couldn’t add the 2x3 to the printer options, but were willing to send me a new roll of 2x2 or 3x3 to make up for the money I spent on a 2x3 that is unusable. Great customer service!

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice little printer
reviews.reviewText: My assumption is these little thermal printers are largely the same.This one is totally fine.I wanted to print a lot of labels and this has exceeded my expectations so far.I've only used it Bluetooth to my phone, it didn't seem to want to be detected by my tablet.the app isn't bad. you get i think 1 ad when you load it up, usually for the brand of labels. it looks like you need an account to be able to save anything, even locally, which is lame. good thing everything so far has been a simple to re-create template.I have not yet tried to print shipping labels with this. i assume if i can get the image loaded into the app i can print it but i'll find out when i need to.connecting it via (included) usb cable might be the way to go to do a lot of labels or text entry but i have no tried it yet. it looks like you need to use a chrome add-on to do it. maybe if its detected as a printer you can just send stuff to it.
